    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 24,
      "content": "Mode of Action"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 25,
      "content": "Solifenacin Succinate is an antimuscarinic agent. It acts by inhibiting muscarinic receptors, which are involved in"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 26,
      "content": "bladder muscle contraction. This action helps to reduce the frequency and urgency of urination associated with"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 27,
      "content": "overactive bladder."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 28,
      "content": "Absorption"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 29,
      "content": "Following oral administration, Solifenacin Succinate is absorbed from the gastrointestinal tract. Peak plasma"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 30,
      "content": "concentrations are typically reached within 1 to 2 hours after dosing. The bioavailability is approximately 55%."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 31,
      "content": "Distribution"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 32,
      "content": "Solifenacin Succinate is distributed throughout the body. It is approximately 98% bound to plasma proteins, primarily"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 33,
      "content": "albumin and alpha-1-acid glycoprotein. The volume of distribution is approximately 113 liters."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 34,
      "content": "Metabolism"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 35,
      "content": "Confidential!"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 1,
      "sn": 36,
      "content": "Page 1"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 2,
      "sn": 37,
      "content": "Solifenacin Succinate undergoes extensive hepatic metabolism, primarily via the cytochrome P450 3A4 (CYP3A4)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 2,
      "sn": 38,
      "content": "enzyme system. The main metabolic pathways include N-dealkylation and O-dealkylation, leading to the formation of"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 2,
      "sn": 39,
      "content": "several metabolites. The primary active metabolite is the N-dealkylated product."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 2,
      "sn": 40,
      "content": "Confidential!"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "section_title": null,
      "page": 2,
